article.headline: San Francisco 82, Portland 73
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Michael Williams and Angelo Caloiaro scored 18 points each to lead San Francisco to an 82-73 victory over Portland on Thursday night. The win kept San Francisco (14-12, 8-3 West Coast) tied with Gonzaga for second in the conference standings, 1 1/2 games behind St. Mary's. Portland (18-9, 5-6) held a 66-63 lead with 4:56 left, but the Dons went on a 13-1 run. The key basket was a 3-pointer by Williams that gave USF a 73-67 lead. Williams had seven points in the last 2 1/2 minutes. Nemanja Mitrovic had 26 points, including four 3-pointers, and six rebounds for the Pilots. Cody Doolin had 14 points and Rashad Green 13 for the Dons.
